	     Johannesburg – Four construction workers were injured when a wall collapsed on them during renovation of a home in Parkmore on Wednesday afternoon, paramedics said.  When paramedics arrived at the scene, the four were found lying in a pile of rubble, surrounded by their colleagues, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement.  They sustained minor to moderate injuries and were treated at the scene before being taken to the Edenvale and Helen Joseph hospitals.    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  